PISA 2018 Dataset Exploration¶

Preliminary Wrangling¶

  • This notebook explores the PISA 2018 dataset found in this link
  • Dataset contains several questionnaires answered by 600k students 100k teachers and 22k schools
  • Each student in this dataset also participates in a cognitive exam that may contain math, reading, science, and financial literacy questions.

Bivariate Exploration¶

In [11]:
Image(filename='./images/6.png')
Out[11]:
  • it seems students' understanding of difficulty is subjective.
  • the more difficult reading is rated, the less we have outliers.
    • might mean they became aware of their strength and weaknesses if they rate something strongly
  • however, ratings between 0-4 has quite a lot of students who received scores less than 200
    • maybe they didn't understand the questionnaire fully as well
In [12]:
Image(filename='./images/7.png')
Out[12]:

  • between genders average score is similar
In [13]:
Image(filename='./images/8.png')
